The paper deals with content-based image retrieval, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of aggregation techniques and binary local features also involves machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects. Finally, the investigation of the combination of aggregated binary features with Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) brings in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
